build: add optional USE_EXTERNAL_LIBDEFLATE

commit.message:
build: add optional USE_EXTERNAL_LIBDEFLATE

When setting USE_EXTERNAL_LIBDEFLATE=1 as a make(1) argument a system
version will be used and otherwise it will use the vendored libdeflate.

build: expand pkg-config variable when used

When using = instead of := the variable is set when its used and not
when its set. This prvents pkg-config from being run even when the value
of the variable is being set by the user as a make(1) argument.

build: all should be the default target

The first build rule is the default rule.
build: add missing PHONY targets
Add Docker build image instructions to README

cli: Silence -Wformat warnings

With GCC-13.1.1 and clang-16.0.4.

cli/cli.cpp:475:51: warning: format specifies type 'long long' but the argument has type 'int64_t' (aka 'long') [-Wformat]
                        sprintf(temp, "%lld -> %lld bytes (%.0f%%)\n", total, written, ratio);
                                       ~~~~                            ^~~~~
                                       %ld
cli/cli.cpp:475:58: warning: format specifies type 'long long' but the argument has type 'int64_t' (aka 'long') [-Wformat]
                        sprintf(temp, "%lld -> %lld bytes (%.0f%%)\n", total, written, ratio);
                                               ~~~~                           ^~~~~~~
                                               %ld

Fix DAX corruption when using libdeflate.

Need to include the zlib header.
Update Actions versions.

Include sample batch files for Windows.

These serve as further documentation and are a common request.

Fixes #63.

Allow piping CRC/similar output.

Note: pipe stderr, not stdout.  Maybe I should change this for the final
success, although it makes sense to send progress to stderr...

Fixes #68.
Fix warning, avoiding small copy.
Merge branch 'build'

Remove macOS dependency step.

lz4 and libuv are already default installed on Actions runners, and
libdeflate will use the repo-tracked one.

Brew is slow, so prefer to skip if possible.

Minor tweaks to actions workflow, correct filename.

Note: the Windows build here is not using PGO, unlike the release build.
Create workflow for code testing and artifact generation
